name: Bulbasaur
description: For some time after its birth, it grows by gaining nourishment from the seed on its back.

name: Ivysaur
description: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower’s coming bloom.

name: Venusaur
description: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.

name: Charmander
description: The fire on the tip of its tail is a measure of its life. If healthy, its tail burns intensely.

name: Charmeleon
description: In the rocky mountains where Charmeleon live, their fiery tails shine at night like stars.

name: Charizard
description: It is said that Charizard’s fire burns hotter if it has experienced harsh battles.

name: Squirtle
description: It shelters itself in its shell then strikes back with spouts of water at every opportunity.

name: Wartortle
description: It is said to live 10,000 years. Its furry tail is popular as a symbol of longevity.

name: Blastoise
description: The jets of water it spouts from the rocket cannons on its shell can punch through thick steel.

name: Caterpie
description: It releases a stench from its red antenna to repel enemies. It grows by molting repeatedly.

name: Metapod
description: A steel-hard shell protects its tender body. It quietly endures hardships while awaiting evolution.

name: Butterfree
description: It loves the honey of flowers and can locate flower patches that have even tiny amounts of pollen.

name: Weedle
description: It eats its weight in leaves every day. It fends off attackers with the needle on its head.

name: Kakuna
description: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

name: Beedrill
description: Its best attack involves flying around at high speed, striking with poison needles, then flying off.

name: Pidgey
description: It is docile and prefers to avoid conflict. If disturbed, however, it can ferociously strike back.

name: Pidgeotto
description: It flies over its wide territory in search of prey, downing it with its highly developed claws.

name: Pidgeot
description: By flapping its wings with all its might, Pidgeot can make a gust of wind capable of bending tall trees.

name: Rattata
description: It searches for food all day. It gnaws on hard objects to wear down its fangs, which grow constantly during its lifetime.

name: Raticate
description: With its long fangs, this surprisingly violent Pokémon can gnaw away even thick concrete with ease.

name: Spearow
description: It flaps its small wings busily to fly. Using its beak, it searches in grass for prey.

name: Fearow
description: It has the stamina to fly all day on its broad wings. It fights by using its sharp beak.

name: Ekans
description: It sneaks through grass without making a sound and strikes unsuspecting prey from behind.

name: Arbok
description: The pattern on its belly is for intimidation. It constricts foes while they are frozen in fear.

name: Pikachu
description: It occasionally uses an electric shock to recharge a fellow Pikachu that is in a weakened state.

name: Raichu
description: Its tail discharges electricity into the ground, protecting it from getting shocked.

name: Sandshrew
description: It digs deep burrows to live in. When in danger, it rolls up its body to withstand attacks.

name: Sandslash
description: The spikes on its body are made up of its hardened hide. It rolls up and attacks foes with its spikes.

name: Nidoran♀
description: While it does not prefer to fight, even one drop of the poison it secretes from barbs can be fatal.

name: Nidorina
description: When it senses danger, it raises all the barbs on its body. These barbs grow slower than Nidorino’s.

name: Nidoqueen
description: Its entire body is armored with hard scales. It will protect the young in its burrow with its life.

name: Nidoran♂
description: It scans its surroundings by raising its ears out of the grass. Its toxic horn is for protection.

name: Nidorino
description: It has a violent disposition and stabs foes with its horn, which oozes poison upon impact.

name: Nidoking
description: One swing of its mighty tail can snap a telephone pole as if it were a matchstick.

name: Clefairy
description: On nights with a full moon, Clefairy gather from all over and dance. Bathing in moonlight makes them float.

name: Clefable
description: Their ears are sensitive enough to hear a pin drop from over a mile away, so they’re usually found in quiet places.

name: Vulpix
description: As each tail grows, its fur becomes more lustrous. When held, it feels slightly warm.

name: Ninetales
description: Each of its nine tails is imbued with supernatural power, and it can live for a thousand years.

name: Jigglypuff
description: Looking into its cute, round eyes makes it start singing a song so pleasant listeners can’t help but fall asleep.

name: Wigglytuff
description: Its fine fur feels so pleasant, those who accidentally touch it cannot take their hands away.

name: Zubat
description: It does not need eyes, because it emits ultrasonic waves to check its surroundings while it flies.

name: Golbat
description: Flitting around in the dead of night, it sinks its fangs into its prey and drains a nearly fatal amount of blood.

name: Oddish
description: It often plants its root feet in the ground during the day and sows seeds as it walks about at night.

name: Gloom
description: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

name: Vileplume
description: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.

name: Paras
description: Mushrooms named tochukaso grow on its back. They grow along with the host Paras.

name: Parasect
description: A mushroom grown larger than the host’s body controls Parasect. It scatters poisonous spores.

name: Venonat
description: Its big eyes are actually clusters of tiny eyes. At night, its kind is drawn by light.

name: Venomoth
description: It flutters its wings to scatter dustlike scales. The scales leach toxins if they contact skin.

name: Diglett
description: A Pokémon that lives underground. Because of its dark habitat, it is repelled by bright sunlight.

name: Dugtrio
description: Its three heads move alternately, driving it through tough soil to depths of over 60 miles.

name: Meowth
description: It is nocturnal in nature. If it spots something shiny, its eyes glitter brightly.

name: Persian
description: A very haughty Pokémon. Among fans, the size of the jewel in its forehead is a topic of much talk.

name: Psyduck
description: When headaches stimulate its brain cells, which are usually inactive, it can use a mysterious power.

name: Golduck
description: When its forehead shines mysteriously, Golduck can use the full extent of its power.

name: Mankey
description: It lives in treetop colonies. If one becomes enraged, the whole colony rampages for no reason.

name: Primeape
description: It grows angry if you see its eyes and gets angrier if you run. If you beat it, it gets even madder.

name: Growlithe
description: Extremely loyal to its Trainer, it will bark at those who approach the Trainer unexpectedly and run them out of town.

name: Arcanine
description: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.

name: Poliwag
description: Its skin is so thin, its internal organs are visible. It has trouble walking on its newly grown feet.

name: Poliwhirl
description: The spiral pattern on its belly subtly undulates. Staring at it gradually causes drowsiness.

name: Poliwrath
description: With its extremely tough muscles, it can keep swimming in the Pacific Ocean without resting.

name: Abra
description: Using its psychic power is such a strain on its brain that it needs to sleep for 18 hours a day.

name: Kadabra
description: It stares at its silver spoon to focus its mind. It emits more alpha waves while doing so.

name: Alakazam
description: The spoons clutched in its hands are said to have been created by its psychic powers.

name: Machop
description: Though small in stature, it is powerful enough to easily heft and throw a number of Geodude at once.

name: Machoke
description: It happily carries heavy cargo to toughen up. It willingly does hard work for people.

name: Machamp
description: Its four muscled arms slam foes with powerful punches and chops at blinding speed.

name: Bellsprout
description: It prefers hot and humid environments. It is quick at capturing prey with its vines.

name: Weepinbell
description: A Pokémon that appears to be a plant. It captures unwary prey by dousing them with a toxic powder.

name: Victreebel
description: It pools in its mouth a fluid with a honey-like scent, which is really an acid that dissolves anything.

name: Tentacool
description: Because its body is almost entirely composed of water, it shrivels up if it is washed ashore.

name: Tentacruel
description: It extends its 80 tentacles to form an encircling poisonous net that is difficult to escape.

name: Geodude
description: At rest, it looks just like a rock. Carelessly stepping on it will make it swing its fists angrily.

name: Graveler
description: It rolls on mountain paths to move. Once it builds momentum, no Pokémon can stop it without difficulty.

name: Golem
description: Even dynamite can’t harm its hard, boulder-like body. It sheds its hide just once a year.

name: Ponyta
description: As a newborn, it can barely stand. However, through galloping, its legs are made tougher and faster.

name: Rapidash
description: When at an all-out gallop, its blazing mane sparkles, enhancing its beautiful appearance.

name: Slowpoke
description: Although slow, it is skilled at fishing with its tail. It does not feel pain if its tail is bitten.

name: Slowbro
description: Though usually dim witted, it seems to become inspired if the Shellder on its tail bites down.

name: Magnemite
description: The electromagnetic waves emitted by the units at the sides of its head expel antigravity, which allows it to float.

name: Magneton
description: The stronger electromagnetic waves from the three linked Magnemite are enough to dry out surrounding moisture.

name: Farfetch'd
description: It can’t live without the stalk it holds. That’s why it defends the stalk from attackers with its life.

name: Doduo
description: The brains in its two heads appear to communicate emotions to each other with a telepathic power.

name: Dodrio
description: When Doduo evolves into this odd breed, one of its heads splits into two. It runs at nearly 40 mph.

name: Seel
description: The colder it gets, the better it feels. It joyfully swims around oceans so cold that they are filled with floating ice.

name: Dewgong
description: Its streamlined body has low resistance, and it swims around cold oceans at a speed of eight knots.

name: Grimer
description: Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

name: Muk
description: It’s so stinky! Muk’s body contains toxic elements, and any plant will wilt when it passes by.

name: Shellder
description: It swims backward by opening and closing its two shells. Its large tongue is always kept hanging out.

name: Cloyster
description: It fights by keeping its shell tightly shut for protection and by shooting spikes to repel foes.

name: Gastly
description: Born from gases, anyone would faint if engulfed by its gaseous body, which contains poison.

name: Haunter
description: It likes to lurk in the dark and tap shoulders with a gaseous hand. Its touch causes endless shuddering.

name: Gengar
description: The leer that floats in darkness belongs to a Gengar delighting in casting curses on people.

name: Onix
description: Opening its large mouth, it ingests massive amounts of soil and creates long tunnels.

name: Drowzee
description: It can tell what people are dreaming by sniffing with its big nose. It loves fun dreams.

name: Hypno
description: Seeing its swinging pendulum can induce sleep in three seconds, even in someone who just woke up.

name: Krabby
description: It lives in burrows dug on sandy beaches. Its pincers fully grow back if they are broken in battle.

name: Kingler
description: The larger pincer has 10,000- horsepower strength. However, it is so heavy, it is difficult to aim.

name: Voltorb
description: It looks just like a Poké Ball. It is dangerous because it may electrocute or explode on contact.

name: Electrode
description: It is known to drift on winds if it is bloated to bursting with stored electricity.

name: Exeggcute
description: Its six eggs converse using telepathy. They can quickly gather if they become separated.

name: Exeggutor
description: It is called “The Walking Jungle.” If a head grows too big, it falls off and becomes an Exeggcute.

name: Cubone
description: When it thinks of its dead mother, it cries. Its crying makes the skull it wears rattle hollowly.

name: Marowak
description: From its birth, this savage Pokémon constantly holds bones. It is skilled in using them as weapons.

name: Hitmonlee
description: Its legs can stretch double. First-time foes are startled by its extensible reach.

name: Hitmonchan
description: The arm-twisting punches it throws pulverize even concrete. It rests after three minutes of fighting.

name: Lickitung
description: Being licked by its long, saliva-covered tongue leaves a tingling sensation. Extending its tongue retracts its tail.

name: Koffing
description: Toxic gas is held within its thin, balloon-shaped body, so it can cause massive explosions.

name: Weezing
description: Inhaling toxic fumes from trash and mixing them inside its body lets it spread an even fouler stench.

name: Rhyhorn
description: Its powerful tackles can destroy anything. However, it is too slow witted to help people work.

name: Rhydon
description: Standing on its hind legs freed its forelegs and made it smarter. It is very forgetful, however.

name: Chansey
description: A kindly Pokémon that lays highly nutritious eggs and shares them with injured Pokémon or people.

name: Tangela
description: Many writhing vines cover it, so its true identity remains unknown. The blue vines grow its whole life long.

name: Kangaskhan
description: It raises its offspring in its belly pouch. It lets the baby out to play only when it feels safe.

name: Horsea
description: It makes its nest in the shade of corals. If it senses danger, it spits murky ink and flees.

name: Seadra
description: Its spines provide protection. Its fins and bones are prized as traditional-medicine ingredients.

name: Goldeen
description: Though it appears very elegant when swimming with fins unfurled, it can jab powerfully with its horn.

name: Seaking
description: In autumn, its body becomes more fatty in preparing to propose to a mate. It takes on beautiful colors.

name: Staryu
description: As long as its red core remains, it can regenerate its body instantly, even if it’s torn apart.

name: Starmie
description: Its core shines in many colors and sends radio signals into space to communicate with something.

name: Mr. Mime
description: It shapes an invisible wall in midair by minutely vibrating its fingertips to stop molecules in the air.

name: Scyther
description: The sharp scythes on its forearms become increasingly sharp by cutting through hard objects.

name: Jynx
description: Its cries sound like human speech. However, it is impossible to tell what it is trying to say.

name: Electabuzz
description: Research is progressing on storing lightning in Electabuzz so this energy can be used at any time.

name: Magmar
description: The scorching fire exhaled by Magmar forms heat waves around its body, making it hard to see the Pokémon clearly.

name: Pinsir
description: It grips prey with its powerful pincers and will not let go until the prey is torn in half.

name: Tauros
description: Once it takes aim at its foe, it makes a headlong charge. It is famous for its violent nature.

name: Magikarp
description: A Magikarp living for many years can leap a mountain using Splash. The move remains useless, though.

name: Gyarados
description: Once it begins to rampage, a Gyarados will burn everything down, even in a harsh storm.

name: Lapras
description: Able to understand human speech and very intelligent, it loves to swim in the sea with people on its back.

name: Ditto
description: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.

name: Eevee
description: Thanks to its unstable genetic makeup, this special Pokémon conceals many different possible evolutions.

name: Vaporeon
description: Its cell composition is similar to water molecules. As a result, it can’t be seen when it melts away into water.

name: Jolteon
description: By storing electricity in its body, it can shoot its bristlelike fur like a barrage of missiles.

name: Flareon
description: Inhaled air is carried to its flame sac, heated, and exhaled as fire that reaches over 3,000 degrees F.

name: Porygon
description: A man-made Pokémon created using advanced scientific means. It can move freely in cyberspace.

name: Omanyte
description: A Pokémon that was resurrected from a fossil using modern science. It swam in ancient seas.

name: Omastar
description: It is thought that this Pokémon became extinct because its spiral shell grew too large.

name: Kabuto
description: It is thought to have inhabited beaches 300 million years ago. It is protected by a stiff shell.

name: Kabutops
description: It is thought that this Pokémon came onto land because its prey adapted to life on land.

name: Aerodactyl
description: A Pokémon that roamed the skies in the dinosaur era. Its teeth are like saw blades.

name: Snorlax
description: When its belly is full, it becomes too lethargic to even lift a finger, so it is safe to bounce on its belly.

name: Articuno
description: A legendary bird Pokémon. It can create blizzards by freezing moisture in the air.

name: Zapdos
description: A legendary Pokémon that is said to live in thunderclouds. It freely controls lightning bolts.

name: Moltres
description: One of the legendary bird Pokémon. It is said that its appearance indicates the coming of spring.

name: Dratini
description: It is called the “Mirage Pokémon” because so few have seen it. Its shed skin has been found.

name: Dragonair
description: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.

name: Dragonite
description: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

name: Mewtwo
description: A Pokémon created by recombining Mew’s genes. It’s said to have the most savage heart among Pokémon.

name: Mew
description: Because it can use all kinds of moves, many scientists believe Mew to be the ancestor of Pokémon.

name: Chikorita
description: It uses the leaf on its head to determine the temperature and humidity. It loves to sunbathe.

name: Bayleef
description: The buds that ring its neck give off a spicy aroma that perks people up.

name: Meganium
description: Its breath has the fantastic ability to revive dead plants and flowers.

name: Cyndaquil
description: It has a timid nature. If it is startled, the flames on its back burn more vigorously.

name: Quilava
description: It intimidates foes with the heat of its flames. The fire burns more strongly when it readies to fight.

name: Typhlosion
description: It attacks using blasts of fire. It creates heat shimmers with intense fire to hide itself.

name: Totodile
description: It has the habit of biting anything with its developed jaws. Even its Trainer needs to be careful.

name: Croconaw
description: Once it bites down, it won’t let go until it loses its fangs. New fangs quickly grow into place.

name: Feraligatr
description: It usually moves slowly, but it goes at blinding speed when it attacks and bites prey.

name: Sentret
description: It has a very nervous nature. It stands up high on its tail so it can scan wide areas.

name: Furret
description: The mother puts its offspring to sleep by curling up around them. It corners foes with speed.

name: Hoothoot
description: It marks time precisely. Some countries consider it to be a wise friend, versed in the world’s ways.

name: Noctowl
description: Its eyes are specially developed to enable it to see clearly even in murky darkness and minimal light.

name: Ledyba
description: It is so timid, it can’t move if it isn’t with a swarm of others. It conveys its feelings with scent.

name: Ledian
description: It uses starlight as energy. When more stars appear at night, the patterns on its back grow larger.

name: Spinarak
description: It sets a trap by spinning a web with thin but strong silk. It waits motionlessly for prey to arrive.

name: Ariados
description: It attaches silk to its prey and sets it free. Later, it tracks the silk to the prey and its friends.

name: Crobat
description: Having four wings allows it to fly more quickly and quietly so it can sneak up on prey without its noticing.

name: Chinchou
description: It discharges positive and negative electricity from its antenna tips to shock its foes.

name: Lanturn
description: Lanturn’s light can shine up from great depths. It is nicknamed “The Deep-Sea Star.”

name: Pichu
description: The electric sacs in its cheeks are small. If even a little electricity leaks, it becomes shocked.

name: Cleffa
description: According to local rumors, Cleffa are often seen in places where shooting stars have fallen.

name: Igglybuff
description: Its body has a faintly sweet scent and is bouncy and soft. If it bounces even once, it cannot stop.

name: Togepi
description: It transforms the kindness and joy of others into happiness, which it stores in its shell.

name: Togetic
description: To share its happiness, it flies around the world seeking kind- hearted people.

name: Natu
description: It picks food from cactus plants, deftly avoiding buds and spines. It seems to skip about to move.

name: Xatu
description: This odd Pokémon can see both the past and the future. It eyes the sun’s movement all day.

name: Mareep
description: When cold weather increases static electricity, its wool doubles in size and the tip of its tail glows slightly.

name: Flaaffy
description: Not even downy wool will grow on its rubbery, nonconductive patches of skin that prevent electrical shock.

name: Ampharos
description: The tip of its tail shines so brightly it can be used to send sea-navigation beacons to distant foreign shores.

name: Bellossom
description: When the heavy rainfall season ends, it is drawn out by warm sunlight to dance in the open.

name: Marill
description: The oil-filled tail functions as a buoy, so it’s fine even in rivers with strong currents.

name: Azumarill
description: Its long ears are superb sensors. It can distinguish the movements of things in water and tell what they are.

name: Sudowoodo
description: To avoid being attacked, it does nothing but mimic a tree. It hates water and flees from rain.

name: Politoed
description: It gathers groups of others as their leader. Its cries make Poliwag obey.

name: Hoppip
description: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

name: Skiploom
description: It blooms when the weather warms. It floats in the sky to soak up as much sunlight as possible.

name: Jumpluff
description: Blown by seasonal winds, it circles the globe, scattering cotton spores as it goes.

name: Aipom
description: It lives high among the treetops. It can use its tail as freely and cleverly as its hands.

name: Sunkern
description: It suddenly falls out of the sky in the morning. Knowing it’s weak, it simply feeds until it evolves.

name: Sunflora
description: Since it converts sunlight into energy, it is always looking in the direction of the sun.

name: Yanma
description: By flapping its wings at high speed, it can fly freely through the air. Even sudden stops are no problem.

name: Wooper
description: When walking on land, it covers its body with a poisonous film that keeps its skin from dehydrating.

name: Quagsire
description: It has an easygoing nature. It doesn’t care if it bumps its head on boats and boulders while swimming.

name: Espeon
description: Its fur is so sensitive, it can feel minute shifts in the air and predict the weather...and its foes’ thoughts.

name: Umbreon
description: When exposed to the moon’s aura, the rings on its body glow faintly and it’s filled with a mysterious power.

name: Murkrow
description: If spotted, it will lure an unwary person into chasing it then lose the pursuer on mountain trails.

name: Slowking
description: Being bitten by Shellder gave it intelligence comparable to that of award-winning scientists.

name: Misdreavus
description: A Pokémon that startles people in the middle of the night. It gathers fear as its energy.

name: Unown
description: When alone, nothing happens. However, if there are two or more, an odd power is said to emerge.

name: Wobbuffet
description: It desperately tries to keep its black tail hidden. It is said to be proof the tail hides a secret.

name: Girafarig
description: The head on its tail contains a small brain. It can instinctively fight even while facing backward.

name: Pineco
description: It looks just like a pinecone. Its shell protects it from bird Pokémon that peck it by mistake.

name: Forretress
description: It is encased in a steel shell. Its peering eyes are all that can be seen of its mysterious innards.

name: Dunsparce
description: It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted, it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.

name: Gligar
description: It clamps on to its chosen prey then jabs the stinger on its tail into the prey while it’s stunned with surprise.

name: Steelix
description: The iron it ingested with the soil it swallowed transformed its body and made it harder than diamonds.

name: Snubbull
description: Small Pokémon flee from its scary face. It is, however, considered by women to be cute.

name: Granbull
description: It is timid in spite of its looks. If it becomes enraged, however, it will strike with its huge fangs.

name: Qwilfish
description: It shoots the poison spines on its body in all directions. Its round form makes it a poor swimmer.

name: Scizor
description: It raises its pincers with eyelike markings for intimidation. It also swings them down dangerously.

name: Shuckle
description: The berries stored in its vaselike shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.

name: Heracross
description: No matter how heavy its opponents, it flings them far away with its prized horn.

name: Sneasel
description: A smart and sneaky Pokémon, it makes its opponents flinch by suddenly showing the claws hidden in its paws.

name: Teddiursa
description: It lets honey soak into its paws so it can lick them all the time. Every set of paws tastes unique.

name: Ursaring
description: In its territory, it leaves scratches on trees that bear delicious berries or fruits.

name: Slugma
description: Its body is made of magma. If it doesn’t keep moving, its body will cool and harden.

name: Magcargo
description: Its body temperature is roughly 18,000 degrees F. Flames spout from gaps in its hardened shell.

name: Swinub
description: Rooting the tip of its snout into the ground, it searches for food. Sometimes it even digs up a hot spring.

name: Piloswine
description: With its excellent sense of smell, it’s even able to find mushrooms that are buried under frozen ground.

name: Corsola
description: They prefer unpolluted southern seas. Their coral branches lose their color and deteriorate in dirty water.

name: Remoraid
description: The water they shoot from their mouths can hit moving prey from more than 300 feet away.

name: Octillery
description: It has a tendency to want to be in holes. It prefers rock crags or pots and sprays ink from them before attacking.

name: Delibird
description: It carries food all day long. When someone is lost in the mountains, it shares that food.

name: Mantine
description: If it builds up enough speed swimming, it can fly over 300 feet out of the water from the surface of the ocean.

name: Skarmory
description: Its heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light, so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph.

name: Houndour
description: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

name: Houndoom
description: The flames it breathes when angry contain toxins. If they cause a burn, it will hurt forever.

name: Kingdra
description: It lives in caves on the seafloor and creates giant whirlpools every time it moves.

name: Phanpy
description: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.

name: Donphan
description: It attacks by curling up then rolling into its foe. It can blow apart a house in one hit.

name: Porygon2
description: It was upgraded to enable the exploration of other planets. However, it failed to measure up.

name: Stantler
description: Staring at its antlers creates an odd sensation as if one were being drawn into their centers.

name: Smeargle
description: It marks its territory by using its tail like a paintbrush. There are more than 5,000 different marks.

name: Tyrogue
description: It is famous for its eagerness to fight and always nurses injuries from challenging larger foes.

name: Hitmontop
description: It fights while spinning like a top. The centrifugal force boosts its destructive power by 10.

name: Smoochum
description: It tests everything by touching with its lips, which remember what it likes and dislikes.

name: Elekid
description: Spinning its arms around to generate electricity makes the area between its horns shine light blue.

name: Magby
description: It’s small, but its body temperature is over 1,100 degrees F. Embers escape its mouth and nose when it breathes.

name: Miltank
description: It is said that kids who drink Miltank’s milk grow up to become hearty, healthy adults.

name: Blissey
description: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.

name: Raikou
description: It is said to have fallen with lightning. It can fire thunderbolts from the rain clouds on its back.

name: Entei
description: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

name: Suicune
description: It races around the world to purify fouled water. It dashes away with the north wind.

name: Larvitar
description: Born deep underground, it comes aboveground and becomes a pupa once it has finished eating the surrounding soil.

name: Pupitar
description: This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.

name: Tyranitar
description: The quakes caused when it walks make even great mountains crumble and change the surrounding terrain.

name: Lugia
description: It sleeps in a deep-sea trench. If it flaps its wings, it is said to cause a 40-day storm.

name: Ho-Oh
description: Its feathers are in seven colors. It is said that anyone seeing it is promised eternal happiness.

name: Celebi
description: It has the power to travel across time, but it is said to appear only in peaceful times.

name: Treecko
description: The soles of its feet are covered by countless tiny spikes, enabling it to walk on walls and ceilings.

name: Grovyle
description: It lives in dense jungles. While closing in on its prey, it leaps from branch to branch.

name: Sceptile
description: The leaves that grow on its arms can slice down thick trees. It is without peer in jungle combat.

name: Torchic
description: A fire burns inside, so it feels very warm to hug. It launches fireballs of 1,800 degrees F.

name: Combusken
description: Its kicking mastery lets it loose 10 kicks per second. It emits sharp cries to intimidate foes.

name: Blaziken
description: Flames spout from its wrists, enveloping its knuckles. Its punches scorch its foes.

name: Mudkip
description: To alert it, the fin on its head senses the flow of water. It has the strength to heft boulders.

name: Marshtomp
description: Its sturdy legs give it sure footing, even in mud. It burrows into dirt to sleep.

name: Swampert
description: It can swim while towing a large ship. It bashes down foes with a swing of its thick arms.

name: Poochyena
description: A Pokémon with a persistent nature, it chases its chosen prey until the prey becomes exhausted.

name: Mightyena
description: It chases down prey in a pack. It will never disobey the commands of a skilled Trainer.

name: Zigzagoon
description: It walks in zigzag fashion. It is good at finding items in the grass and even in the ground.

name: Linoone
description: It charges prey at speeds over 60 mph. However, because it can only run straight, it often fails.

name: Wurmple
description: Often targeted by bird Pokémon, it desperately resists by releasing poison from its tail spikes.

name: Silcoon
description: It wraps silk around the branches of a tree. It drinks rainwater on its silk while awaiting evolution.

name: Beautifly
description: Despite its looks, it is aggressive. It jabs with its long, thin mouth if disturbed while collecting pollen.

name: Cascoon
description: It never forgets any attack it endured while in the cocoon. After evolution, it seeks payback.

name: Dustox
description: Toxic powder is scattered with each flap. At night, it is known to strip leaves off trees lining boulevards.

name: Lotad
description: It looks like an aquatic plant and serves as a ferry to Pokémon that can’t swim.

name: Lombre
description: It has a mischievous spirit. If it spots an angler, it will tug on the fishing line to interfere.

name: Ludicolo
description: If it hears festive music, all its muscles fill with energy. It can’t help breaking out into a dance.

name: Seedot
description: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon.

name: Nuzleaf
description: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in forests.

name: Shiftry
description: By flapping its leafy fan, it can whip up gusts of 100 ft/second that can level houses.

name: Taillow
description: It has a gutsy spirit that makes it bravely take on tough foes. It flies in search of warm climates.

name: Swellow
description: It circles the sky in search of prey. When it spots one, it dives steeply to catch the prey.

name: Wingull
description: It makes its nest on sheer cliffs. Riding the sea breeze, it glides up into the expansive skies.

name: Pelipper
description: Skimming the water’s surface, it dips its large bill in the sea, scoops up food and water, and carries it.

name: Ralts
description: If its horns capture the warm feelings of people or Pokémon, its body warms up slightly.

name: Kirlia
description: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.

name: Gardevoir
description: To protect its Trainer, it will expend all its psychic power to create a small black hole.

name: Surskit
description: It appears as if it is skating on water. It draws prey with a sweet scent from the tip of its head.

name: Masquerain
description: Its antennae have eye patterns on them. Its four wings enable it to hover and fly in any direction.

name: Shroomish
description: It spouts poison spores from the top of its head. These spores cause pain all over if inhaled.

name: Breloom
description: Its short arms stretch when it throws punches. Its technique is equal to that of pro boxers.

name: Slakoth
description: If it eats just three leaves in a day, it is satisfied. Other than that, it sleeps for 20 hours a day.

name: Vigoroth
description: Its heartbeat is fast and its blood so agitated that it can’t sit still for one second.

name: Slaking
description: This Pokémon lives lying on its side. It only rolls over and moves when there is no more grass to eat.

name: Nincada
description: It grows underground, sensing its surroundings using antennae instead of its virtually blind eyes.

name: Ninjask
description: Because it moves so quickly, it sometimes becomes unseeable. It congregates around tree sap.

name: Shedinja
description: A discarded bug shell that came to life. Peering into the crack on its back is said to steal one’s spirit.

name: Whismur
description: Usually, its cries are like quiet murmurs. If frightened, it shrieks at the same volume as a jet plane.

name: Loudred
description: The shock waves from its cries can tip over trucks. It stamps its feet to power up.

name: Exploud
description: Its howls can be heard over six miles away. It emits all sorts of noises from the ports on its body.

name: Makuhita
description: It toughens its body by slamming into thick trees. Many snapped trees can be found near its nest.

name: Hariyama
description: It loves to match power with big-bodied Pokémon. It can knock a truck flying with its arm thrusts.

name: Azurill
description: It swings its large, nutrient-filled tail around to fight opponents bigger than itself.

name: Nosepass
description: Its magnetic nose always faces north and draws iron objects to its body to protect itself better.

name: Skitty
description: It shows its cute side by chasing its own tail until it gets dizzy.

name: Delcatty
description: The reason it does not have a nest is that it simply searches for a clean, comfortable place then sleeps there.

name: Sableye
description: It hides in the darkness of caves. Its diet of gems has transformed its eyes into gemstones.

name: Mawile
description: Attached to its head is a huge set of jaws formed by horns. It can chew through iron beams.

name: Aron
description: In order to build up its steel body, it eats iron ore. This pesky Pokémon is known to eat railroad tracks.

name: Lairon
description: Lairon fight over territory, and when their steel bodies collide, sparks fly.

name: Aggron
description: It claims an entire mountain as its own. The more wounds it has, the more it has battled, so don’t take it lightly.

name: Meditite
description: It always trains deep in mountains. It levitates when it heightens its spiritual power through meditation.

name: Medicham
description: It gains the ability to see the aura of its opponents by honing its mind through starvation.

name: Electrike
description: Using electricity stored in its fur, it stimulates its muscles to heighten its reaction speed.

name: Manectric
description: It discharges electricity from its mane. It creates a thundercloud overhead to drop lightning bolts.

name: Plusle
description: It cheers on friends with pom-poms made of sparks. It drains power from telephone poles.

name: Minun
description: It cheers on friends. If its friends are losing, its body lets off more and more sparks.

name: Volbeat
description: It communicates with others by lighting up its rear at night. It loves Illumise’s sweet aroma.

name: Illumise
description: With its sweet aroma, it guides Volbeat to draw signs with light in the night sky.

name: Roselia
description: It uses the different poisons in each hand separately when it attacks. The stronger its aroma, the healthier it is.

name: Gulpin
description: Almost all its body is its stomach. Its harsh digestive juices quickly dissolve anything it swallows.

name: Swalot
description: It swallows anything whole. It sweats toxic fluids from its follicles to douse foes.

name: Carvanha
description: They swarm any foe that invades their territory. Their sharp fangs can tear out boat hulls.

name: Sharpedo
description: Its fangs rip through sheet iron. It swims at 75 mph and is known as “The Bully of the Sea.”

name: Wailmer
description: It eats one ton of food every day. It plays by shooting stored seawater out its blowholes with great force.

name: Wailord
description: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.

name: Numel
description: The magma in its body reaches 2,200 degrees F. Its hump gets smaller when it uses Fire-type moves.

name: Camerupt
description: The volcanoes on its back have a major eruption every 10 years--or whenever it becomes really angry.

name: Torkoal
description: It burns coal inside its shell for energy. It blows out black soot if it is endangered.

name: Spoink
description: Using its tail like a spring, it keeps its heart beating by bouncing constantly. If it stops, it dies.

name: Grumpig
description: It uses black pearls to amplify its psychic power. It does a strange dance to control foes’ minds.

name: Spinda
description: No two Spinda have the same pattern of spots. Its tottering step fouls the aim of foes.

name: Trapinch
description: It makes an inescapable conical pit and lies in wait at the bottom for prey to come tumbling down.

name: Vibrava
description: The ultrasonic waves it generates by rubbing its two wings together cause severe headaches.

name: Flygon
description: Known as “The Desert Spirit,” this Pokémon hides in the sandstorms it causes by beating its wings.

name: Cacnea
description: By storing water in its body, this desert dweller can survive for 30 days without water.

name: Cacturne
description: It becomes active at night, seeking prey that is exhausted from the day’s desert heat.

name: Swablu
description: For some reason, it likes to land on people’s heads softly and act like it’s a hat.

name: Altaria
description: On sunny days, it flies freely through the sky and blends into the clouds. It sings in a beautiful soprano.

name: Zangoose
description: It’s Seviper’s archrival. To threaten those it encounters, it fans out the claws on its front paws.

name: Seviper
description: Constant polishing makes the edge of the blade on its tail extremely sharp. It’s Zangoose’s archrival.

name: Lunatone
description: The phase of the moon apparently has some effect on its power. It’s active on the night of a full moon.

name: Solrock
description: Solar energy is the source of its power, so it is strong during the daytime. When it spins, its body shines.

name: Barboach
description: Its slimy body is hard to grasp. In one region, it is said to have been born from hardened mud.

name: Whiscash
description: It is extremely protective of its territory. If any foe approaches, it attacks using vicious tremors.

name: Corphish
description: No matter how dirty the water in the river, it will adapt and thrive. It has a strong will to survive.

name: Crawdaunt
description: Loving to battle, this Pokémon pinches all Pokémon that enter its territory with its pincers and throws them out.

name: Baltoy
description: Discovered in ancient ruins, it moves by spinning around and forms a group when it finds others.

name: Claydol
description: This mysterious Pokémon started life as an ancient clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.

name: Lileep
description: It lived on the seafloor 100 million years ago and was reanimated scientifically.

name: Cradily
description: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.

name: Anorith
description: A Pokémon ancestor that was reanimated from a fossil. It lived in the sea and hunted with claws.

name: Armaldo
description: It went ashore after evolving. Its entire body is clad in a sturdy armor.

name: Feebas
description: It is a shabby and ugly Pokémon. However, it is very hardy and can survive on little water.

name: Milotic
description: Its lovely scales are described as rainbow colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.

name: Castform
description: Temperature and weather affect its cellular structure, so this Pokémon changes form according to the weather.

name: Kecleon
description: It can freely change its body’s color. The zigzag pattern on its belly doesn’t change, however.

name: Shuppet
description: It feeds on the dark emotions of sadness and hatred, which make it grow steadily stronger.

name: Banette
description: A doll that became a Pokémon over its grudge of being thrown away. It seeks the child who disowned it.

name: Duskull
description: It loves the crying of children. It startles bad kids by passing through walls and making them cry.

name: Dusclops
description: It seeks drifting will-o’-the-wisps and sucks them into its empty body. What happens inside is a mystery.

name: Tropius
description: It flies by flapping its broad leaves and gives the sweet, delicious fruit around its neck to children.

name: Chimecho
description: Its cries echo inside its hollow body to emerge as beautiful notes for startling and repelling foes.

name: Absol
description: It appears from deep in the mountains to warn people about upcoming disasters it has sensed with its horn.

name: Wynaut
description: It grows strong by pushing up against others en masse. It loves eating sweet fruit.

name: Snorunt
description: It is said that several Snorunt gather under giant leaves and live together in harmony.

name: Glalie
description: It prevents prey from escaping by instantaneously freezing moisture in the air.

name: Spheal
description: They can’t swim well yet, and they move much faster by rolling. When they’re happy, they clap fins.

name: Sealeo
description: Be it Spheal or Poké Ball, it will spin any round object on its nose with the greatest of ease.

name: Walrein
description: Not only does its thick blubber keep it warm, it also protects it from attacks. It shatters ice with its prized tusks.

name: Clamperl
description: It makes a single pearl during its lifetime. The pearl is said to amplify psychic power.

name: Huntail
description: It lives deep in the sea. With a tail shaped like a small fish, it attracts unsuspecting prey.

name: Gorebyss
description: It lives at the bottom of the sea. In the springtime, its pink body turns more vivid for some reason.

name: Relicanth
description: A rare Pokémon discovered during a deep-sea exploration. It has not changed in over 100 million years.

name: Luvdisc
description: It lives in warm seas. It is said that a couple finding this Pokémon will be blessed with eternal love.

name: Bagon
description: Dreaming of one day flying, it practices by leaping off cliffs every day.

name: Shelgon
description: Within its rugged shell, its cells have begun changing. The shell peels off the instant it evolves.

name: Salamence
description: As a result of its long-held dream of flying, its cellular structure changed, and wings grew out.

name: Beldum
description: Its cells are all magnetic, and it communicates with others by using magnetic pulses.

name: Metang
description: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked, amplifying its psychic power.

name: Metagross
description: With four linked brains, it’s more intelligent than a supercomputer, and it uses calculations to analyze foes.

name: Regirock
description: Its entire body is made of rock. If any part chips off in battle, it attaches rocks to repair itself.

name: Regice
description: Its body is made of ice from the ice age. It controls frigid air of -328 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Registeel
description: Tempered by pressure underground over tens of thousands of years, its body cannot be scratched.

name: Latias
description: Its body is covered with a down that can refract light in such a way that it becomes invisible.

name: Latios
description: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

name: Kyogre
description: It is said to have widened the seas by causing downpours. It had been asleep in a marine trench.

name: Groudon
description: It had been asleep in underground magma ever since it fiercely fought Kyogre long ago.

name: Rayquaza
description: It lives in the ozone layer far above the clouds and cannot be seen from the ground.

name: Jirachi
description: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.

name: Deoxys
description: An alien virus that fell to earth on a meteor underwent a DNA mutation to become this Pokémon.

name: Turtwig
description: The shell on its back is made of soil. On a very healthy Turtwig, the shell should feel moist.

name: Grotle
description: It knows where pure water wells up. It carries fellow Pokémon there on its back.

name: Torterra
description: Some Pokémon are born on a Torterra’s back and spend their entire life there.

name: Chimchar
description: It is very agile. Before going to sleep, it extinguishes the flame on its tail to prevent fires.

name: Monferno
description: It skillfully controls the intensity of the fire on its tail to keep its foes at an ideal distance.

name: Infernape
description: It uses unique fighting moves with fire on its hands and feet. It will take on any opponent.

name: Piplup
description: A poor walker, it often falls down. However, its strong pride makes it puff up its chest without a care.

name: Prinplup
description: Because every Prinplup considers itself to be the most important, they can never form a group.

name: Empoleon
description: If anyone were to hurt its pride, it would slash them with wings that can cleave through an ice floe.

name: Starly
description: Because they are weak individually, they form groups. However, they bicker if the group grows too big.

name: Staravia
description: Recognizing their own weakness, they always live in a group. When alone, a Staravia cries noisily.

name: Staraptor
description: It never stops attacking even if it is injured. It fusses over the shape of its comb.

name: Bidoof
description: A comparison revealed that Bidoof’s front teeth grow at the same rate as Rattata’s.

name: Bibarel
description: A river dammed by Bibarel will never overflow its banks, which is appreciated by people nearby.

name: Kricketot
description: Its legs are short. Whenever it stumbles, its stiff antennae clack with a xylophone-like sound.

name: Kricketune
description: There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokémon.

name: Shinx
description: The extension and contraction of its muscles generates electricity. It glows when in trouble.

name: Luxio
description: Strong electricity courses through the tips of its sharp claws. A light scratch causes fainting in foes.

name: Luxray
description: It can see clearly through walls to track down its prey and seek its lost young.

name: Budew
description: Sensitive to changing temperatures, the bud blooms when it’s warm, releasing toxic pollen.

name: Roserade
description: Luring prey with a sweet scent, it uses poison whips on its arms to poison, bind, and finish off the prey.

name: Cranidos
description: A lifelong jungle dweller from 100 million years ago, it would snap obstructing trees with head butts.

name: Rampardos
description: If two were to smash their heads together, their foot-thick skulls would keep them from fainting.

name: Shieldon
description: It is outstandingly armored. As a result, it can eat grass and berries without having to fight.

name: Bastiodon
description: When they lined up side by side, no foe could break through. They shielded their young in that way.

name: Burmy
description: Even if it is born where there are no cocooning materials, it somehow always ends up with a cloak.

name: Wormadam
description: When evolving, its body takes in surrounding materials. As a result, there are many body variations.

name: Mothim
description: While it loves floral honey, it won’t gather any itself. Instead, it plots to steal some from Combee.

name: Combee
description: This Pokémon is a set of three. When they sleep, they gather up and form a giant hive of 100 Combee.

name: Vespiquen
description: It houses its colony in cells in its body and releases various pheromones to make those grubs do its bidding.

name: Pachirisu
description: A pair may be seen rubbing their cheek pouches together in an effort to share stored electricity.

name: Buizel
description: It inflates the flotation sac around its neck and pokes its head out of the water to see what is going on.

name: Floatzel
description: It is a common sight around fishing ports. It is known to rescue people and carry off prey.

name: Cherubi
description: The small ball is not only filled with nutrients, it is also tasty. Starly try to peck it off.

name: Cherrim
description: If it senses strong sunlight, it opens its folded petals to absorb the sun’s rays with its whole body.

name: Shellos
description: Beware of pushing strongly on its squishy body, as it makes a mysterious purple fluid ooze out.

name: Gastrodon
description: Long ago, its entire back was shielded with a sturdy shell. There are traces of it left in its cells.

name: Ambipom
description: Split into two, the tails are so adept at handling and doing things, Ambipom rarely uses its hands.

name: Drifloon
description: These Pokémon are called the “Signpost for Wandering Spirits.” Children holding them sometimes vanish.

name: Drifblim
description: They carry people and Pokémon, but the wind can catch them, so there can’t be a fixed destination.

name: Buneary
description: By extending its rolled-up ears and striking the ground, it can bound so high it surprises itself.

name: Lopunny
description: Extremely cautious, it quickly bounds off when it senses danger.

name: Mismagius
description: Its cry sounds like an incantation. It is said the cry may rarely be imbued with happiness-giving power.

name: Honchkrow
description: If one utters a deep cry, many Murkrow gather quickly. For this, it is called “Summoner of Night.”

name: Glameow
description: It hides its spiteful tendency of hooking its claws into the nose of its Trainer if it isn’t fed.

name: Purugly
description: It binds its body with its tails to make itself look bigger. If it locks eyes, it will glare ceaselessly.

name: Chingling
description: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

name: Stunky
description: It sprays a foul fluid from its rear. Its stench spreads over a mile radius, driving Pokémon away.

name: Skuntank
description: It attacks by spraying a horribly smelly fluid from the tip of its tail. Attacks from above confound it.

name: Bronzor
description: They are found in ancient tombs. The patterns on their backs are said to be imbued with mysterious power.

name: Bronzong
description: In ages past, this Pokémon was revered as a bringer of rain. It was found buried in the ground.

name: Bonsly
description: It prefers an arid atmosphere. It leaks water that looks like tears when adjusting its moisture level.

name: Mime Jr.
description: It mimics the expressions and motions of those it sees to understand the feelings of others.

name: Happiny
description: It likes to carry around a small rock. It may wander around others’ feet and cause them to stumble.

name: Chatot
description: Its tongue is just like a human’s. As a result, it can cleverly mimic human speech.

name: Spiritomb
description: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.

name: Gible
description: It attacks using its huge mouth. While its attacks are powerful, it hurts itself out of clumsiness, too.

name: Gabite
description: It loves sparkly things. It seeks treasures in caves and hoards the loot in its nest.

name: Garchomp
description: It is said that when one runs at high speed, its wings create blades of wind that can fell nearby trees.

name: Munchlax
description: In its desperation to gulp down food, it forgets about the food it has hidden under its fur.

name: Riolu
description: It uses the shapes of auras, which change according to emotion, to communicate with others.

name: Lucario
description: By reading the auras of all things, it can tell how others are feeling from over half a mile away.

name: Hippopotas
description: It shuts its nostrils tight then travels through sand as if walking. They form colonies of around 10.

name: Hippowdon
description: It is surprisingly quick to anger. It holds its mouth agape as a display of its strength.

name: Skorupi
description: It lives in arid regions and can go without food for a year while waiting for prey.

name: Drapion
description: It takes pride in its strength. Even though it can tear foes apart, it finishes them off with powerful poison.

name: Croagunk
description: Inflating its poison sacs, it fills the area with an odd sound and hits flinching opponents with a poison jab.

name: Toxicroak
description: The croaking that Toxicroak produces before a battle is for churning the poison it has stored in its poison sac.

name: Carnivine
description: Using its tentacles to lash itself to trees, it lies in wait for prey, luring it close with sweet-smelling drool.

name: Finneon
description: The line running down its side can store sunlight. It shines vividly at night.

name: Lumineon
description: It crawls along the seafloor using its long front fins like legs. It competes for food with Lanturn.

name: Mantyke
description: The pattern on its back varies by region. It often swims in a school of Remoraid.

name: Snover
description: Seemingly curious about people, they gather around footsteps they find on snowy mountains.

name: Abomasnow
description: They appear when the snow flowers bloom. When the petals fall, they retreat to places unknown again.

name: Weavile
description: They communicate by clawing signs in boulders and work together to surround enemies.

name: Magnezone
description: Sometimes the magnetism emitted by Magnezone is too strong, making them attract each other so they cannot move.

name: Lickilicky
description: Their saliva contains lots of components that can dissolve anything. The numbness caused by their lick does not dissipate.

name: Rhyperior
description: It can launch a rock held in its hand like a missile by tightening then expanding muscles instantly.

name: Tangrowth
description: Even if one of its arms is eaten, it’s fine. The Pokémon regenerates quickly and will go right back to normal.

name: Electivire
description: The instant it presses the tips of its tails onto an opponent, it sends over 20,000 volts of electricity into the foe.

name: Magmortar
description: When shooting 3,600 degree F fireballs from its arms, its body takes on a whitish hue from the intense heat.

name: Togekiss
description: It shares many blessings with people who respect one another’s rights and avoid needless strife.

name: Yanmega
description: It prefers to battle by biting apart foes’ heads instantly while flying by at high speed.

name: Leafeon
description: With cells similar to those of plants, it performs photosynthesis inside its body and creates pure air.

name: Glaceon
description: It lowers its body heat to freeze its fur. The hairs then become like needles it can fire.

name: Gliscor
description: It dances silently through the sky. When it approaches prey, it can land a critical hit in an instant.

name: Mamoswine
description: When the temperature rose at the end of the ice age, most Mamoswine disappeared.

name: Porygon-Z
description: Its programming was modified to enable work in alien dimensions. It did not work as planned.

name: Gallade
description: When trying to protect someone, it extends its elbows as if they were swords and fights savagely.

name: Probopass
description: It freely controls three units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force.

name: Dusknoir
description: It is said to take lost spirits into its pliant body and guide them home.

name: Froslass
description: It freezes prey by blowing its -58 degrees F breath. It is said to then secretly display its prey.

name: Rotom
description: Its electric-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

name: Uxie
description: When Uxie flew, people gained the ability to solve problems. It was the birth of knowledge.

name: Mesprit
description: When Mesprit flew, people learned the joy and sadness of living. It was the birth of emotions.

name: Azelf
description: When Azelf flew, people gained the determination to do things. It was the birth of willpower.

name: Dialga
description: A legendary Pokémon of Sinnoh. It is said that time flows when Dialga’s heart beats.

name: Palkia
description: A legendary Pokémon of Sinnoh. It is said that space becomes more stable with Palkia’s every breath.

name: Heatran
description: Its body is made of rugged steel. However, it is partially melted in spots because of its own heat.

name: Regigigas
description: It is said to have made Pokémon that look like itself from a special ice mountain, rocks, and magma.

name: Giratina
description: It was banished for its violence. It silently gazed upon the old world from the Distortion World.

name: Cresselia
description: On nights around the quarter moon, the aurora from its tail extends and undulates beautifully.

name: Phione
description: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.

name: Manaphy
description: It is born with a wondrous power that lets it bond with any kind of Pokémon.

name: Darkrai
description: To protect itself, it afflicts those around it with nightmares. However, it means no harm.

name: Shaymin
description: The flowers all over its body burst into bloom if it is lovingly hugged and senses gratitude.

name: Arceus
description: It is said to have emerged from an egg in a place where there was nothing then shaped the world.

name: Victini
description: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being’s entire body will be overflowing with power.

name: Snivy
description: Being exposed to sunlight makes its movements swifter. It uses vines more adeptly than its hands.

name: Servine
description: When it gets dirty, its leaves can’t be used in photosynthesis, so it always keeps itself clean.

name: Serperior
description: It only gives its all against strong opponents who are not fazed by the glare from Serperior’s noble eyes.

name: Tepig
description: It loves to eat roasted berries, but sometimes it gets too excited and burns them to a crisp.

name: Pignite
description: The more it eats, the more fuel it has to make the fire in its stomach stronger. This fills it with even more power.

name: Emboar
description: A flaring beard of fire is proof that it is fired up. It is adept at using many different moves.

name: Oshawott
description: The scalchop on its stomach isn’t just used for battle--it can be used to break open hard berries as well.

name: Dewott
description: As a result of strict training, each Dewott learns different forms for using the scalchops.

name: Samurott
description: In the time it takes a foe to blink, it can draw and sheathe the seamitars attached to its front legs.

name: Patrat
description: Extremely cautious, one of them will always be on the lookout, but it won’t notice a foe coming from behind.

name: Watchog
description: Using luminescent matter, it makes its eyes and body glow and stuns attacking opponents.

name: Lillipup
description: Though it is a very brave Pokémon, it’s also smart enough to check its foe’s strength and avoid battle.

name: Herdier
description: This very loyal Pokémon helps Trainers, and it also takes care of other Pokémon.

name: Stoutland
description: Being wrapped in its long fur is so comfortable that a person would be fine even overnight on a wintry mountain.

name: Purrloin
description: Their cute act is a ruse. They trick people and steal their valuables just to see the looks on their faces.

name: Liepard
description: Their beautiful form comes from the muscles they have developed. They run silently in the night.

name: Pansage
description: It’s good at finding berries and gathers them from all over. It’s kind enough to share them with friends.

name: Simisage
description: It strikes its enemies with a thorn-covered tail. The leaf on its head is bitter.

name: Pansear
description: Very intelligent, it roasts berries before eating them. It likes to help people.

name: Simisear
description: When it gets excited, embers rise from its head and tail and it gets hot. For some reason, it loves sweets.

name: Panpour
description: The water stored inside the tuft on its head is full of nutrients. It waters plants with it using its tail.

name: Simipour
description: It prefers places with clean water. When its tuft runs low, it replenishes it by siphoning up water with its tail.

name: Munna
description: This Pokémon appears before people and Pokémon who are having nightmares and eats those dreams.

name: Musharna
description: The dream mist coming from its forehead changes into many different colors depending on the dream that was eaten.

name: Pidove
description: This very forgetful Pokémon will wait for a new order from its Trainer even though it already has one.

name: Tranquill
description: No matter where in the world it goes, it knows where its nest is, so it never gets separated from its Trainer.

name: Unfezant
description: Males swing the plumage on their heads to threaten others, but females are better at flying.

name: Blitzle
description: Its mane shines when it discharges electricity. They use the frequency and rhythm of these flashes to communicate.

name: Zebstrika
description: When this ill-tempered Pokémon runs wild, it shoots lightning from its mane in all directions.

name: Roggenrola
description: The hexagonal-shaped hole is its ear. It has a tendency to walk in the direction the sound is coming from.

name: Boldore
description: When it is healthy, its core sticks out. Always facing the same way, it swiftly moves front to back and left to right.

name: Gigalith
description: The solar rays it absorbs are processed in its energy core and fired as a ball of light.

name: Woobat
description: The heart-shaped mark left on a body after a Woobat has been attached to it is said to bring good fortune.

name: Swoobat
description: It shakes its tail vigorously when it emits ultrasonic waves strong enough to reduce concrete to rubble.

name: Drilbur
description: By spinning its body, it can dig straight through the ground at a speed of 30 mph.

name: Excadrill
description: Forming a drill with its steel claws and head, it can bore through a steel plate, no matter how thick it is.

name: Audino
description: Using the feelers on its ears, it can tell how someone is feeling or when an egg might hatch.

name: Timburr
description: Always carrying squared logs, they help out with construction. As they grow, they carry bigger logs.

name: Gurdurr
description: With strengthened bodies, they skillfully wield steel beams to take down buildings.

name: Conkeldurr
description: Rather than rely on force, they master moves that utilize the centrifugal force of spinning concrete.

name: Tympole
description: By vibrating its cheeks, it emits sound waves imperceptible to humans and warns others of danger.

name: Palpitoad
description: It lives in the water and on land. It uses its long, sticky tongue to immobilize its opponents.

name: Seismitoad
description: By putting power into its bumps, it creates vibrations and increases the power of its punches.

name: Throh
description: When it encounters a foe bigger than itself, it wants to throw it. It changes belts as it gets stronger.

name: Sawk
description: Desiring the strongest karate chop, they seclude themselves in mountains and train without sleeping.

name: Sewaddle
description: Since this Pokémon makes its own clothes out of leaves, it is a popular mascot for fashion designers.

name: Swadloon
description: Preferring dark, damp places, it spends the entire day eating fallen leaves that lie around it.

name: Leavanny
description: Upon finding a small Pokémon, it weaves clothing for it from leaves by using the sticky silk secreted from its mouth.

name: Venipede
description: Using the feelers on its head and tail, it picks up vibrations in the air to determine its prey’s location and state.

name: Whirlipede
description: Storing energy for evolution, it sits. But, when predators approach, it moves to stab them with poison spikes.

name: Scolipede
description: It clasps its prey with the claws on its neck until it stops moving. Then it finishes it off with deadly poison.

name: Cottonee
description: Perhaps because they feel more at ease in a group, they stick to others they find. They end up looking like a cloud.

name: Whimsicott
description: They appear along with whirlwinds. They pull pranks, such as moving furniture and leaving balls of cotton in homes.

name: Petilil
description: The leaves on its head grow right back even if they fall out. These bitter leaves refresh those who eat them.

name: Lilligant
description: The fragrance of the garland on its head has a relaxing effect, but taking care of it is very difficult.

name: Basculin
description: Red- and blue-striped Basculin are very violent and always fighting. They are also remarkably tasty.

name: Sandile
description: They live hidden under hot desert sands in order to keep their body temperature from dropping.

name: Krokorok
description: Protected by thin membranes, their eyes can see even in the dead of night. They live in groups of a few individuals.

name: Krookodile
description: Very violent Pokémon, they try to clamp down on anything that moves in front of their eyes.

name: Darumaka
description: When it sleeps, it pulls its limbs into its body and its internal fire goes down to 1,100° F.

name: Darmanitan
description: When one is injured in a fierce battle, it hardens into a stone-like form. Then it meditates and sharpens its mind.

name: Maractus
description: When it moves rhythmically, it makes a sound similar to maracas, making the surprised Pokémon flee.

name: Dwebble
description: When it finds a stone of a suitable size, it secretes a liquid from its mouth to open up a hole to crawl into.

name: Crustle
description: When its boulder is broken in battles for territory, it feels unsure and begins to weaken.

name: Scraggy
description: Proud of its sturdy skull, it suddenly headbutts everything, but its weight makes it unstable, too.

name: Scrafty
description: It pulls up its shed skin to protect itself while it kicks. The bigger the crest, the more respected it is.

name: Sigilyph
description: The guardians of an ancient city, they always fly the same route while keeping watch for invaders.

name: Yamask
description: These Pokémon arose from the spirits of people interred in graves. Each retains memories of its former life.

name: Cofagrigus
description: Grave robbers who mistake them for real coffins and get too close end up trapped inside their bodies.

name: Tirtouga
description: This Pokémon was restored from a fossil. It swam skillfully and dove to depths beyond half a mile.

name: Carracosta
description: It could knock out a foe with a slap from one of its developed front appendages and chew it up, shell or bones and all.

name: Archen
description: It was revived from an ancient fossil. Not able to fly, it lived in treetops and hopped from one branch to another.

name: Archeops
description: It runs better than it flies. It takes off into the sky by running at a speed of 25 mph.

name: Trubbish
description: Wanting more garbage, they follow people who litter. They always belch poison gas.

name: Garbodor
description: Consuming garbage makes new kinds of poison gases and liquids inside their bodies.

name: Zorua
description: It changes so it looks just like its foe, tricks it, and then uses that opportunity to flee.

name: Zoroark
description: Stories say those who tried to catch Zoroark were trapped in an illusion and punished.

name: Minccino
description: Minccino greet each other by grooming one another thoroughly with their tails.

name: Cinccino
description: Cinccino’s body is coated in a special oil that helps it deflect attacks, such as punches.

name: Gothita
description: It stares intently at everything. It can become so obsessed with watching that it doesn’t notice attacks.

name: Gothorita
description: According to many old tales, it creates friends for itself by controlling sleeping children on starry nights.

name: Gothitelle
description: It can see the future from the movement of the stars. When it learns its Trainer’s life span, it cries in sadness.

name: Solosis
description: Because their bodies are enveloped in a special liquid, they are fine in any environment, no matter how severe.

name: Duosion
description: When their two divided brains think the same thoughts, their psychic power is maximized.

name: Reuniclus
description: They use psychic power to control their arms, which are made of a special liquid. They can crush boulders psychically.

name: Ducklett
description: They are better at swimming than flying, and they happily eat their favorite food, peat moss, as they dive underwater.

name: Swanna
description: Despite their elegant appearance, they can flap their wings strongly and fly for thousands of miles.

name: Vanillite
description: Theoretically, this Pokémon formed from icicles bathed in energy from the morning sun. Their breath is -58° F.

name: Vanillish
description: They cool down the surrounding air and create ice particles, which they use to freeze their foes.

name: Vanilluxe
description: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and, when angry, cause violent blizzards.

name: Deerling
description: Their coloring changes according to the seasons and can be slightly affected by the temperature and humidity as well.

name: Sawsbuck
description: They migrate according to the seasons, so some people call Sawsbuck the harbingers of spring.

name: Emolga
description: It glides on its outstretched membrane while shocking foes with the electricity stored in the pouches on its cheeks.

name: Karrablast
description: For some reason they evolve when they receive electrical energy while they are attacking Shelmet.

name: Escavalier
description: Wearing the shell covering they stole from Shelmet, they defend themselves and attack with two lances.

name: Foongus
description: It lures Pokémon with its pattern that looks just like a Poké Ball then releases poison spores.

name: Amoonguss
description: It moves the caps on both arms and does a dance to lure prey. It prefers damp places.

name: Frillish
description: If its veil-like arms stun and wrap a foe, that foe will be dragged miles below the surface, never to return.

name: Jellicent
description: Its body is mostly seawater. It’s said there’s a castle of ships Jellicent have sunk on the seafloor.

name: Alomomola
description: It gently holds injured and weak Pokémon in its fins. Its special membrane heals their wounds.

name: Joltik
description: Since it can’t generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity.

name: Galvantula
description: It creates barriers from electrified silk that stun foes. This works as a weapon as well as a defense.

name: Ferroseed
description: It absorbs the iron it finds in the rock while clinging to the ceiling. It shoots spikes when in danger.

name: Ferrothorn
description: By swinging around its three spiky feelers and shooting spikes, it can obliterate an opponent.

name: Klink
description: Two bodies comprise a fixed pair. They spin around each other to generate energy.

name: Klang
description: A minigear and big gear comprise its body. If the minigear it launches at a foe doesn’t return, it will die.

name: Klinklang
description: The minigear spins at high speed. Then the energy from the red core charges the minigear to make it ready to fire.

name: Tynamo
description: One alone can emit only a trickle of electricity, so a group of them gathers to unleash a powerful electric shock.

name: Eelektrik
description: It wraps itself around its prey and paralyzes it with electricity from the round spots on its sides. Then it chomps.

name: Eelektross
description: It latches on to prey with its sucker mouth, sinking in its fangs and shocking the prey with powerful electricity.

name: Elgyem
description: Rumors of its origin are linked to a UFO crash site in the desert 50 years ago.

name: Beheeyem
description: Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three fingers, but those patterns haven’t been decoded.

name: Litwick
description: Its flame is usually out, but it starts shining when it absorbs life force from people or Pokémon.

name: Lampent
description: The spirits it absorbs fuel its baleful fire. It hangs around hospitals waiting for people to pass on.

name: Chandelure
description: The spirits burned up in its ominous flame lose their way and wander this world forever.

name: Axew
description: Its large tusks have a tendency to break, but each time they grow back, they grow in harder and sturdier.

name: Fraxure
description: A broken tusk will not grow back, so it diligently sharpens its tusks on river rocks after the end of a battle.

name: Haxorus
description: Its tusks are incredibly destructive. They can easily slice through a thick, sturdy steel column every time.

name: Cubchoo
description: Their snot is a barometer of health. When healthy, their snot is sticky and the power of their ice moves increases.

name: Beartic
description: They love the cold seas of the north. They create pathways across the ocean waters by freezing their own breath.

name: Cryogonal
description: They are composed of ice crystals. They capture prey with chains of ice, freezing the prey at -148° F.

name: Shelmet
description: When it and Karrablast are together, and both receive electrical stimulation, they both evolve.

name: Accelgor
description: When its body dries out, it weakens. So it wraps a membrane around itself for protection while it spits poison.

name: Stunfisk
description: When its opponent can’t be paralyzed, it contorts itself with unexpected speed and flops away.

name: Mienfoo
description: It takes pride in the speed at which it can use moves. What it loses in power, it makes up for in quantity.

name: Mienshao
description: Using the long fur on its arms like whips, it launches into combo attacks that, once started, no one can stop.

name: Druddigon
description: It runs through the narrow tunnels formed by Excadrill and Onix. It uses its sharp claws to catch prey.

name: Golett
description: Ancient science fashioned this Pokémon from clay. It’s been active for thousands of years.

name: Golurk
description: Golurk were created to protect people and Pokémon. They run on a mysterious energy.

name: Pawniard
description: Ignoring their injuries, groups attack by sinking the blades that cover their bodies into their prey.

name: Bisharp
description: This pitiless Pokémon commands a group of Pawniard to hound prey into immobility. It then moves in to finish the prey off.

name: Bouffalant
description: They are known to charge so wildly that if a train were to enter their territory, they would send it flying.

name: Rufflet
description: It stands up to massive opponents, not out of courage, but out of recklessness. But that is how it gets stronger.

name: Braviary
description: For the sake of its friends, this brave warrior of the sky will not stop battling, even if injured.

name: Vullaby
description: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.

name: Mandibuzz
description: They fly in circles around the sky. When they spot prey, they attack and carry it back to their nest with ease.

name: Heatmor
description: It draws in air through its tail, transforms it into fire, and uses it like a tongue. It melts Durant and eats them.

name: Durant
description: Individuals each play different roles in driving Heatmor, their natural predator, away from their colony.

name: Deino
description: Lacking sight, it’s unaware of its surroundings, so it bumps into things and eats anything that moves.

name: Zweilous
description: The two heads do not get along. Whichever head eats more than the other gets to be the leader.

name: Hydreigon
description: It responds to movement by attacking. This scary, three-headed Pokémon devours everything in its path!

name: Larvesta
description: Said to have been born from the sun, it spews fire from its horns and encases itself in a cocoon of fire when it evolves.

name: Volcarona
description: Thought to be an embodiment of the sun, it appeared during a bitterly cold winter and saved Pokémon from freezing.

name: Cobalion
description: It has a body and heart of steel. It worked with its allies to punish people when they hurt Pokémon.

name: Terrakion
description: Spoken of in legend, this Pokémon used its phenomenal power to destroy a castle in its effort to protect Pokémon.

name: Virizion
description: Legends say this Pokémon confounded opponents with its swift movements.

name: Tornadus
description: In every direction it flies, creating winds so powerful, they blow everything away.

name: Thundurus
description: As it flies around, it shoots lightning all over the place and causes forest fires. It is therefore disliked.

name: Reshiram
description: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with fire. It helps those who want to build a world of truth.

name: Zekrom
description: This legendary Pokémon can scorch the world with lightning. It assists those who want to build an ideal world.

name: Landorus
description: From the forces of lightning and wind, it creates energy to give nutrients to the soil and make the land abundant.

name: Kyurem
description: This legendary ice Pokémon waits for a hero to fill in the missing parts of its body with truth or ideals.

name: Keldeo
description: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.

name: Meloetta
description: The melodies sung by Meloetta have the power to make Pokémon that hear them happy or sad.

name: Genesect
description: This Pokémon existed 300 million years ago. Team Plasma altered it and attached a cannon to its back.
